  "body": "Once you do a build with `npm run build` the index.html gets CSS and JS files from the root.\r\nThis is  because there is a forward slash in the src/href:\r\n\r\n`<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/static/js/main.0bcc9445.js\"></script>`\r\n`<link href=\"/static/css/main.65027555.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">`\r\n\r\nRunning the index.html on local or remote server doesn't work if the App is not in the root folder and throws a 404 error on the required files.\r\n\r\nThe correct path should be relative:\r\n`<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"static/js/main.0bcc9445.js\"></script>`\r\n`<link href=\"static/css/main.65027555.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">`\r\n`<link rel=\"manifest\" href=\"manifest.json\">`\r\n`<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"favicon.ico\">`\r\n\r\nThis way if you have your project into a sub folder, the App can grab the `static` folder content.\r\n\r\nThis is true as of React v15.6.1",
